index 93e6136..a6151fd 100644
--- a/RULES.md
+++ b/RULES.md
@@ -231,6 +231,7 @@ To guarantee engineering excellence, UI/UX accessibility, and strict adherence t
 | **46. Mobile Settings & Modals Positioning Override (`100% Profile & Top Accessibility`)** | **+ Solved Mobile Settings Clipping (`"on mobile the settings should start a little bit lowe bcs the profie it not showing at all"`):** Previously, `#menu-modal .modal-box` relied on `align-items: center` vertically inside `.modal-overlay`. On mobile screens (`@media max-width: 780px`), when a tall modal (`max-height: 86vh`) centered vertically, its top edge pushed up underneath the mobile browser status bar or phone notch, pushing `#menu-profile-card` (the profile identity card at the top) out of the visible viewport! Enforced explicit mobile top positioning inside `style.css`: `.modal-overlay { align-items: flex-start !important; padding: 38px 6px 24px 6px !important; }` and `#menu-modal .modal-box { margin-top: 12px !important; }`.<br>**+ Instant Profile Population:** Added `updateProfileUI();` right inside `btnMenu.addEventListener('click')` inside `game.js`. Whenever `☰ MENU` opens on smartphone or desktop, the modal window starts exactly ~$50\text{px}$ below the top edge of the screen (`start a little bit lower`), displaying `#menu-profile-card` prominently right at the top! | **- Vertical Scrolling on Short Screens:** Modals on small phones may need scrolling.<br>👉 *Mitigation:* Added `overflow-y: auto !important; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch !important;` on both `.modal-overlay` and `.modal-box`! |
 | **47. Friend Invite Acceptance Hub (`#invite-accept-modal`) & Low Network Cellular Grace Buffer (`45s Reconnect Window`)** | **+ Dedicated Friend Invite Acceptance Hub (`"where is a place to accept the link while your friend is waiting"`):** Added a 5th prominent action button right inside `☰ MENU` (`.menu-modes-grid`): **`📥 ACCEPT FRIEND INVITE (ENTER CODE / LINK)`** (`#btn-accept-invite`). Clicking it opens `#invite-accept-modal` featuring a clean text input (`#invite-code-input`) where your friend can enter the room code (`DUEL-4921`) or paste the full invitation URL (`https://.../?room=DUEL-4921`) while the host waits inside `#online-waiting-modal`. Our parser intelligently strips URL queries/prefixes and connects `join_invite_room` cleanly!<br>**+ Low Network Cellular Grace Buffer (`"remember to hamndle low network from one frind"`):** Replaced immediate disconnect forfeits inside `server.js` with our **45-Second Network Grace Buffer**. When a player experiences a temporary cellular signal drop (`socket.on('disconnect')`), `server.js` marks `room.isPausedForNetwork = true` and emits `opponent_network_lag` (`📶 FRIEND ON LOW NETWORK SIGNAL: Waiting to resume... 45s`) to the connected friend. If the disconnected friend reconnects (`reconnect_to_match`) within 45 seconds, `server.js` reattaches their new socket ID and emits `match_resumed_from_lag`, continuing the live match synchronously with zero lost target progress! | **- Opponent Wait Time:** Players wait up to 45 seconds before a forfeit occurs during signal drops.<br>👉 *Mitigation:* Displayed a real-time countdown (`#lag-timer`) inside `#network-lag-banner` right on the middle board so players see the exact reconnect status! |
 | **48. Host Room Persistence & Re-Attachment (`Solves Polling -> WebSocket Upgrade Wiping Host Room`)** | **+ Solved Host Stale Socket & Room Wiping (`"the host send a link very nice then he accept but nothing happen in the host... the host need to stay in the room waiting"`):** When a host (`Role 1`) clicked `INVITE FRIEND via LINK`, Socket.io connected via HTTP long polling (`socket.id = ABC-123`) and created `inviteRooms['DUEL-XXXX']`. ~1.5s later (or when switching apps to share on WhatsApp), Socket.io upgraded to WebSockets (`socket.id = XYZ-789`), firing `socket.on('disconnect')` for the old polling socket. Because `server.js` immediately deleted `inviteRooms[socket.roomId]` on disconnect, the host's waiting room was wiped while they sat looking at the radar screen! Furthermore, even when the room survived, `hostSocket.emit('match_found')` emitted to the dead `ABC-123` socket ID.<br>**+ 3-Part Host Survival Engine (`server.js` & `game.js`):**<br>• **1st (`5-Minute Survival Grace`)**: Replaced immediate deletion in `server.js` (`disconnect`) with a 5-minute survival window (`cleanupTimer`), keeping `inviteRooms[roomCode]` alive when a host's transport upgrades or briefly drops.<br>• **2nd (`Host Heartbeat Re-Attachment`)**: Added `socket.on('maintain_invite_room')` in `server.js` and a 2.5s maintenance loop (`window._inviteMaintainInterval`) in `game.js`. If the host's socket ID upgrades or re-establishes while waiting (`isOnlineMode && onlineRole === 1`), `server.js` immediately updates `invRoom.host = socket; invRoom.hostId = socket.id; socket.join(roomCode);`!<br>• **3rd (`Exact Room Broadcast`)**: When `join_invite_room` runs, `server.js` emits BOTH to `hostSocket` AND to `io.to(roomCode).emit('match_found_broadcast', ...)` while `game.js` listens for `match_found_broadcast`. This guarantees that 100% of the time, the host receives the match trigger synchronously right alongside their friend! | **- Server Memory for Orphaned Rooms:** If a host closes the app permanently, the invite room stays in memory for 5 minutes.<br>👉 *Mitigation:* Kept our strict DOS hard limit (`max 500 rooms`), explicit 5-minute timeout (`cleanupTimer`), and 15-minute sweep loop inside `server.js`! |
+| **49. Auto-Retry Connection Watchdog & Stripping of Render/Supabase Technical Bloat (`Pure Player-Facing Utility`)** | **+ Solved Stuck "Connecting to DUEL-#" Status (`"it keep saying connecting to duel-# and stops there"`):** Previously, if a player clicked `🚀 ACCEPT INVITE` right while `socket` was initially connecting or transitioning between polling/WebSockets, `join_invite_room` could get dropped or delayed without automatic retries. Added **`window._acceptWatchdog` (Auto-Retry Connection Watchdog)** inside `game.js`: while `#invite-accept-modal` is active, every $1.8\text{s}$ the watchdog checks connection status, automatically re-emits `join_invite_room`, and provides real-time progress (`Trying to connect to host room...` / `Could not reach room... ask your friend if the room is open`).<br>**+ Stripped Technical Bloat for Useful Connection Tips (`"remove that thing if you waiting... about render superbase... say something useful like how you can make a quick connection"`):** Completely removed developer-facing deployment jargon (`"Cloud Server Offline... If you deployed to Netlify without hosting server.js on Render/Railway..."`) across `#online-status-msg`. Replaced with **`⚡ QUICK CONNECTION TIPS`**: clear, player-friendly guidance (`• Check Network Signal`, `• Fast 1v1 Pairing via Invite Link`, `• Instant Practice via AI Bot`)! | **- Repeated Socket Emissions During Lag:** Watchdog re-emits join attempts up to 6 times.<br>👉 *Mitigation:* `server.js` handles duplicate `join_invite_room` calls gracefully by verifying active room state and instantly resending `match_found_broadcast` if the match is already established! |
 
 ### 🛠️ Claude's 11-Step Deep Re-Check Audit Checklist:
 1. **✅ Clean Separation Check:** Verify zero `<style>...</style>` or `<script>...</script>` blocks exist across HTML files (`index.html` and `zonke.html` purely link to external `style.css` and `game.js`).
